motto: The life of the land is perpetuated in righteousness
Our liberties we prize and our rights we will maintain
Let us be grateful to God
By the sword we seek peace but peace only under liberty
If you seek a pleasant peninsula look about you
Let the welfare of the people be the supreme law
To be rather than to seem
One sows for the benefit of another age
With God all things are possible
She flies with her own wings
While I breathe I hope Ready in soul and resource
Freedom and Unity - May the fourteenth star shine bright
